# Kit workflow

Read before non-trivial tasks when Agent Dev Kit is installed.

**User global rules** (`~/.cursor/rules/`) take precedence when stricter.

## Flow

1. Classify intent (feature / bug / refactor / audit).
2. Follow [docs/guidelines/WORKFLOW.md](../agent_dev_kit/docs/guidelines/WORKFLOW.md).
3. **Spec first** — write `.ai/*-spec.md`, get human approval ([SPECS.md](../agent_dev_kit/docs/guidelines/SPECS.md)).
4. **Plan** — write `.ai/*-plan.md` with Detail: minimal | standard | detailed; wait for approval before production code.
5. **TDD** — implement per [TESTING.md](../agent_dev_kit/docs/guidelines/TESTING.md).
6. **Verification** — separate agent session before commit ([VERIFICATION.md](../agent_dev_kit/docs/guidelines/VERIFICATION.md)).
7. **Review** — [REVIEW.md](../agent_dev_kit/docs/guidelines/REVIEW.md) before commit or PR.

